<h2>Presentation and Audio</h2>

The environments have been <strong>completely rebuilt with upgraded graphics</strong> — improved water effects, detailed vegetation, dynamic fire, and a redesigned Sonic model that's leaner than the original's wider proportions. The main menu runs at 60 FPS with fire effects and uses the <strong>Crush 40 version of "Seven Rings in Hand"</strong> as its theme, while the options screen follows the visual style of modern Sonic titles.

The soundtrack expands on what was already considered one of Sonic's best. Each world now has <strong>15+ compositions</strong> including two additional remixes per world for challenge missions. Standout tracks include the Act 2 remix of Pirate Storm (inspired by Dragon's Lair from Black Knight) and the Act 3 remix of Levitated Ruin.

Voice acting is available in <strong>English, Japanese, and Spanish</strong> (Spanish still in progress), with subtitles in nine languages. The original storybook-style cutscenes are preserved, featuring Jason Griffith's performance as Sonic — widely praised for capturing his confident, playful personality.

<h2>Known Limitations</h2>

Project Reignition is still in active development, and there are a few rough edges worth noting. <strong>Performance optimization is ongoing</strong> — players on modest hardware or certain AMD GPU configurations may experience stuttering, particularly during first launches as assets cache. Some sections in Levitated Ruin feel constrained by automated light paths that limit player agency. And while removing motion controls is overwhelmingly the right call, a few reviewers note it does strip away some of the original's novelty factor — though almost nobody considers that a meaningful trade-off.

<h2>Project Reignition FAQ</h2>

<div class="details-grid">
<details>
<summary>What is Project Reignition?</summary>
<p>A fan-made remake of <strong>Sonic and the Secret Rings</strong> (Wii, 2007) built in the Godot engine. It replaces all motion controls with modern gamepad input, rebuilds the graphics, redesigns the skill system, and adds new content including custom music and exclusive skills.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Is the full game playable?</summary>
<p>Six of seven worlds are complete with all missions and three boss fights. Night Palace, the Prologue, and the Darkspine Sonic final boss are still being developed.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>What controller should I use?</summary>
<p>Xbox, PlayStation, Switch, and Steam Deck controllers all work natively. Keyboard and mouse are also supported, but a gamepad is strongly recommended since the game was designed around analog controls and triggers.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Does it run on Steam Deck?</summary>
<p>Yes. Download the Linux build, add it as a non-Steam game through Desktop Mode, and launch it from Gaming Mode. Performance may vary depending on the scene.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Are there performance issues?</summary>
<p>Some stuttering may occur on first launch as assets cache — performance improves on subsequent plays. There are reported incompatibilities with certain AMD drivers. The team is actively optimizing.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>How is this different from the Wii original?</summary>
<p>Full analog controls, free camera, hold-based Speed/Time Break, 50+ redesigned skills with new additions (Quick Step, Double Jump, Light Speed Dash), rebuilt graphics, custom soundtrack remixes, multilingual voice acting, and major quality-of-life fixes throughout.</p>
</details>
</div>
